.TH "usb_disable_endpoint" 9 "usb_disable_endpoint" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
usb_disable_endpoint \- - Disable an endpoint by address
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" usb_disable_endpoint
.BI "(struct usb_device *dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int epaddr "  ","
.BI "bool reset_hardware "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the device whose endpoint is being disabled
.IP "epaddr" 12
the endpoint's address.  Endpoint number for output,
endpoint number + USB_DIR_IN for input
.IP "reset_hardware" 12
flag to erase any endpoint state stored in the
controller hardware
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Disables the endpoint for URB submission and nukes all pending URBs.
If \fIreset_hardware\fP is set then also deallocates hcd/hardware state
for the endpoint.
